<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12203f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12203f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12203f"> 203(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cesse de &mdash; / compl&egrave;tement vides</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&lsquo;<i>Un p&egrave;re a toujours raison</i>&rsquo;]</font>: Un jeune gar&ccedil;on allait tout le temps dans la brousse les mains compl&egrave;tement vides. Son p&egrave;re lui dit: &ldquo;Mon enfant, <mark>cesse d&apos;aller dans la brousse les mains compl&egrave;tement vides</mark>, sans m&ecirc;me avoir sur toi la moindre aiguille.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[A young boy always went into the forest with hands that were completely empty. His father said to him: &ldquo;My child, stop going into the forest with hands that are completely empty, without a single needle.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 26</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
